body.description: FH Group got you covered! Our full set of premium cloth car seat covers not only provides the best protection for your car's upholstery against any type of mess but also enhances the looks of your car's interior. No need to worry anymore about spills, stains, mud, or anything damaging your original car seats because this car seat protector got your back. This full set of car seat covers includes two front low back seat covers, which are compatible with most sedans, SUVs, and vans’ seats with removable headrests only. Our rear seat covers are fully compatible with 50/50, 40/60, or 60/40 split rear benches or longer benches. The cover features 3 zippers in the backrest AND bottom, and extra mesh pieces so you can move the rear seat freely or use the middle armrests and get full protection. We understand messes happen, and that’s why these waterproof and washable seat covers for cars are convenient for any type of driver. We offer automotive seat covers in numerous fabrics, colors, and designs, so you can easily find the seat cover for cars that fits your style the most. We have car seat covers for women, men, and for everyone! FH Group car seat covers are a great car interior accessory for your vehicle. We have it all: car seat covers for SUV, car seat covers for autos, car seat covers for vans, you name it!

FH Group Car Seat Covers Q&A Will the covers fit my car? Consider your car’s main features, such as removable headrests, seatbelt location, split back seat, and more, to ensure a good fit. FH Group also offers custom-fit car seat covers. Do they work w/ heated seats? Yes, FH Group’s car seat covers are compatible with heated seats, so you can protect your car seats while staying cozy. Are they machine washable? Yes, most of our car seat covers are machine washable, except for synthetic leather covers. The tag on the covers has more details on how to wash/clean your seat covers properly. Are they airbag compatible? Yes, most of FH Group's seat covers are airbag-compatible (it's officially tested!). Please check the product's features to see if a specific car seat cover is airbag compatible. Do they fit rear split bench? Yes, our back seat covers are designed to fit 50/50, 40/60, or 60/40 split benches, featuring 3 zippers on the backrest and bottom seat cover. We also offer 2-piece solid bench seat covers. Do they have headrest opening? Some of our low-back seat covers don’t come with pre-cut openings . However, making them is simple (we explain how in our installation videos). Please check the product features to see if you need this adjustment. Do they have seatbelt opening? Not all of our universal-fit seat covers come with openings for seatbelt buckles. Please watch out installation videos to see how to cut an opening for seatbelt buckles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2022
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. 8th gen (‘06) honda civicReally just posting this to help out the next person in the way that this review would’ve helped me out when shopping. Long story short it was a used car the previous owner didn’t even clean ever and the seats had cig burn marks, caked leg/head sweat etc. (many hours of cleaning). I already wanted seat covers but definitely after that. Used car probs *shrug.* After looking at many sets of seat covers I chose to check these out.The all black gives it a clean fresh look and would be easy to wash or replace. Taking out the bench in an 8th gen civic is two clicks, as you can see in the video I also took out the panels between the back rest that folds forward and the doors, as well as the backrest bolts. It may not be necessary but I wanted to do it well the first time, and get as seamless of a look as possible. Bonus: I used one of the headrest covers to cover the armrest so that everything could match exactly.I know I said long story short but in case anyone is HOH I want them to know what’s going on (in the video) as well. I’m not sure if I want to give 4 or 5 stars because there are a few things I feel a little picky about but it’s a universal seat cover so for value for money, and doing great months later, it was a great buy that I would purchase again. So I’ll give 5.Oh! Lastly- The underside of the material is designed so that it doesN’T slide all around. So if you’re yanking on the straps to get the material to smooth itself out, easy way to cause rips and tears. Just TAKE your TIME and it should be fine

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the blood, sweat and tears. 😂
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Ok, so I’m going to try and be as detailed as possible here and set you up for realistic expectations.I recently got a new 2019 Ram 1500 Classic, the Ignition Orange edition. I’m a huge Halloween lover so the black and orange called to me. I’m absolutely obsessed with it! And I wish I could baby it forever.But I’m a Mama.And life happens.And so does fast food or long trips states away to visit family.So I wanted to protect my seats, but I also didn’t want to spend a fortune.All the options I could find with orange/black were like 500$ or more. And I just couldn’t justify that at this time. My thinking in ordering these was:”If I buy these and they suck? I can return them. If they rip, break, get stained or need replaced in a couple years? It would still be worth the savings. And it would give me the opportunity to see if I value this sort of color combo and protection enough to invest in a more expensive option. “That said, I obviously bought them. 😂First thing I will say... I literally bled putting these on. One still has a blood spot on it. 😅Meh. 🤷🏻‍♀️I recommend these if and only if:1. You don’t mind a lot, A LOT, of finagling.2. You have a very keen eye for detail.3. To you, an hour of maneuvering and a couple blood drops from hitting your hands on things under and around seats and tying straps and tucking is worth the savings in money to you.Now, if you fit those requirements: keep reading.Straight to it? These are cheap, thin and you will work your shiny, hiney off getting them on. If you just try and throw them on real quick, they will look like trash. Period. It’s unavoidable.Side note: For my model truck, I have a bench seat in front with a lift up console area that exposes the middle of the seat. This set does not have a cover for that center area but I didn’t mind because I have the console down covering that area a lot and I was mainly worried about protecting the back seat from spills.Back to it...you will have to pinch fabric and pull down, pinch and pull down, repeatedly, and tuck things and pull straps and tighten and tie things in unorthodox ways. (Also a tie down strap may break off. One of mine did.)In my pictures, I actually should get back in and work more on the back seat where the zipper is because it’s puckered a bit how I have it at the moment. Also, I used a full size head rest cover —haphazardly tucked and squished— on the tiny head rest in the middle of the back seat. It could use some pinning still, but my hand was bleeding from knocking it on things multiple times, tucking down in between the seats/tying things down under and I just said “that’ll do pig”. 😂All of that said, once done, these look bad booty Judy. I mean REAL bad mamma jamma, if you know what I’m sayin’. Especially from outside looking in or walking through a parking lot, it looks like I paid a crap ton for custom seat covers and I’ve gotten a lot of compliments. I legit blew my husbands mind, he thought I was nuts and now he’s itching for me to install some in our Challenger.So, bottom line: If you’re up for a ride, some hard work, and have band aids on hand? Get em. Rock em. Join me in Pumpkin land. 🎃 Or whatever land you happen to reside in, not sure if this review will show on other color options. 👌In closing, I hope this was informational and helpful! If so, drop a helpful vote under my review. Let’s me know I’m doing something right. Oh and I bought these with my own money, received no discount or compensation of any kind. I’m just a frugal lady who thought I’d give them a shot! Thanks for reading!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Poor quality. Worst smelling item I’ve ever smelt. Toxic odor that was unbearable. Disappointed.
reviews.reviewText: Was so exited to get new seat covers for my 2009 Subaru Forester. My golden retriever makes a mess constantly so I thought this set of seat covers was going to be exactly what I needed. The first item I put on was the steering wheel cover. I have never used one so once again I was exited to upgrade. As soon as I unwrapped the covers they all had the worst toxic chemical intense smell to them. I reluctantly decided to put the covers on my car because I needed them big time and ASAP. I put the two front seat covers on and the steering wheel and couldn’t handle the toxic odor. It literally made me and my twin brother ill. We both noticed from touching the seat covers and installing them that the god awful smell wouldn’t wash of our hands. I’m dead serious. Both of us smelled like the disgusting odor. I thought I’d try one more time so the next day me and my brother got in my car and we drove less than a mile and the smell was so bad of chemicals, I pulled over and we ripped all the covers and threw them in a dumpster. If you or anyone who rides in you’re car with you has lung issues or gets headaches easy (which I have neither of those issues) I highly recommend not purchasing this set of covers. I literally got the worst headache I’ve ever had and I’m 42 years old. Normally I don’t write reviews, but this I couldn’t pass up cause of how disappointed, and that’s an understatement of these poor quality toxic cheaply made seat cover set. I wish I could get my money back, but me and my brother couldn’t handle another second with those smelly chemical Oder. If others either don’t smell what we did, then there lucky, but there’s no way they couldn’t if they got what I paid for. The customers who are enjoying them and satisfied you must had got a good batch or have bad sinuses. I wish I was in the smallest bit satisfied but I’ve never been more dissatisfied in purchasing a product. Save you’re lungs and money and buy some car seat covers that are better quality. These are not durable covers regardless of the chemical odor. I still don’t have seat covers but I’d rather breath than worry about dog hair and dirt. Plus I didn’t even want my dog lying on the backseat cover, so she wouldn’t smell like them. I wouldn’t even give a star for this poor quality item. Get nose plugs if you order the set I did. Stay safe and healthy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Makes my car look brand new and covers the seats well. Would recommend

I like these seat covers. They go well with my blue 2019 ram 1500. They can be a bit tricky to install. I didnt nick my knuckles as much as i thought i would but definitely can see how that would happen. Lots of maneuvers. If you take the time to really pin everything down and tuck things away then these seat covers look custom. I havent installed the back seat ones totally yet. Front ones are 80% done. Theres still some areas id like to go back and do again. Pretty confident it will be awesome when its done. The fabric is thin but surprisingly durable. There were times pulling on it i thought it would rip. But it didnt. I also cut areas for a better fit, like around the backseat buckles and it didnt rip further. It was surprising. Still fabric is quite thin. But i do like them. I am happy with it.

It's not a perfect fit for a 2017 BMW X1. The seat adjustment buttons for the front seats cannot be accessed. The rear bench design is a little angled towards the back. Overall, I got it just to protect the leather (beige) from getting brown and soiled. The entire rear bench has to be removed and only then the seat cover fixed. And for the X1, that would take half a day. I am yet to get that done!! I would not recommend this for a 2017 BMW X1. However, the quality, colour combination etc matches perfectly well with the car interiors.
